#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn7.16"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.16:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.16:0.2"
msgid "2. Upāsakavagga "
msgstr "2. Lay Followers "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.16:0.3"
msgid "16. Paccanīkasutta "
msgstr "16. The Contraphile "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.179, sc1
msgctxt "sn7.16:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.16:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena paccanīkasāto nāma brāhmaṇo sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati. "
msgstr "Now at that time a brahmin named Contraphile, who loved contradiction, was residing in Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.16:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho paccanīkasātassa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Contraphile thought, "

msgctxt "sn7.16:1.4"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkameyyaṃ. "
msgstr "“Why don’t I go to the ascetic Gotama and "

#. VAR: tadevassāhaṃ → tadeva sāhaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: paccanīkāssan”ti → paccanikāssanti (s1-3) | paccanīkassanti (pts1) | paccanīkasātanti (mr)
msgctxt "sn7.16:1.5"
msgid "Yaṃ yadeva samaṇo gotamo bhāsissati taṃ tadevassāhaṃ paccanīkāssan”ti. "
msgstr "contradict everything he says?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.16:1.6"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā abbhokāse caṅkamati. "
msgstr "At that time the Buddha was walking meditation in the open air. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.16:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho paccanīkasāto brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ caṅkamantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the brahmin Contraphile went up to the Buddha, and said to him as he was walking meditation, "

msgctxt "sn7.16:1.8"
msgid "“bhaṇa samaṇadhamman”ti. "
msgstr "“Ascetic, preach the Dhamma.” "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.386, sc2
msgctxt "sn7.16:2.1"
msgid "“Na paccanīkasātena, "
msgstr "“Fine words aren’t easy to understand "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.16:2.2"
msgid "suvijānaṃ subhāsitaṃ; "
msgstr "by a lover of contradiction, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.16:2.3"
msgid "Upakkiliṭṭhacittena, "
msgstr "whose mind is tainted "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.16:2.4"
msgid "sārambhabahulena ca. "
msgstr "and full of aggression. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn7.16:3.1"
msgid "Yo ca vineyya sārambhaṃ, "
msgstr "But when you’ve dispelled aggression, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.16:3.2"
msgid "appasādañca cetaso; "
msgstr "and your suspicious mind, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.16:3.3"
msgid "Āghātaṃ paṭinissajja, "
msgstr "and you’ve got rid of resentment, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sa ve → sace (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn7.16:3.4"
msgid "sa ve jaññā subhāsitan”ti. "
msgstr "then you’ll understand fine words.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn7.16:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, paccanīkasāto brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the brahmin Contraphile said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn7.16:4.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! … "

msgctxt "sn7.16:4.3"
msgid "upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
